Major data structures:

thread_linkage (ipc.h): node containing pointers.
thread_table (ipc_util.h): threaded hash table, handled by table manager.

Thread table is used for the following:
  ipc_message_table
  ipc_port_table
  ipc_seat_table
  ipc_zone_table

API:
  ipc_thread_create()
  ipc_thread_destroy()
  ipc_thread_append(): add item to the end
  ipc_thread_prepend(): add item to the front
  ipc_thread_lookup(): find a match in the table
  ipc_thread_forward_lookup(): reset get_next() to search from proper starting point
  ipc_thread_get_next()
  ipc_thread_get_prev()
  ipc_thread_get_head()
  ipc_thread_precede()
  ipc_thread_get_current(): get current item in thread hash table
  ipc_thread_set_current(): set current item of table to specified item
  ipc_thread_yank(): remove item from table
  ipc_thread_yank_head(): remove first item from table
  ipc_thread_lock(): lock an item (manage its refcount field.
                   Inserting an item increases the refcount.
                   Removing an item decreases the refcount.

ipc_error_code ipc_send_message (ipc_message *message,
                                 ipc_port_info *dest_port_info)
{
    (*dest_port_info->port_send_vector)(message, dest_port_info);
    return (IPC_OK);
}


dest_port_info->port_send_vector is either:
  - ip_send_reliable_message()
  - ip_send_unreliable_message()
